This mall caters to mostly malay customers.They sell malay traditional outfits etc etc.Frankly speaking,nothing much in the mall.Old building too.Maybe need to bring in more shops and also need to refurbish.
The ladies room need improvement. Please look into it seriously as it's really having bad image of muslim in hygiene and more important the cleanliness over all

The place to go looking for linen, from tapestry to cushions, from curtains to cloths of all colours, shapes & sizes. Three floors with lots of choices for Malay clothes, jewellery, household & decorative items. Rates are reasonable. Ample parking at the annex building (though without lifts).
